<%- include('partials/header') %>

    <div class="page-container">
        <div class="page-header">
            <h1>📝 Guestbook</h1>
            <p class="subtitle">Vulnerability: Stored Cross-Site Scripting / XSS (A03:2021)</p>
        </div>

        <div class="card">
            <form method="POST" action="/guestbook">
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="name">Your Name</label>
                    <input type="text" id="name" name="name" class="form-control" placeholder="Enter your name"
                        required>
                </div>
                <div class="form-group">
                    <label for="message">Message</label>
                    <textarea id="message" name="message" class="form-control" placeholder="Write something..."
                        required></textarea>
                </div>
                <button type="submit" class="btn btn-primary">Post Comment</button>
            </form>
        </div>

        <div class="comment-list">
            <h3 class="mb-2">💬 Comments (<%= comments.length %>)</h3>
            <% comments.forEach(function(c) { %>
                <div class="comment-item">
                    <div class="comment-meta">
                        <span class="comment-author"><%- c.name %></span>
                        <span class="comment-date">
                            <%= c.created_at %>
                        </span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="comment-body"><%- c.message %></div>
                </div>
                <% }); %>
        </div>

        <div class="hint-box">
            <button class="hint-toggle">💡 Show Attack Hints</button>
            <div class="hint-content">
                <h4>🧠 How Stored XSS Works (Simple Explanation)</h4>
                <p>
                    When you post a comment, the website saves it to the database. When anyone visits this page,
                    the comment is displayed <strong>exactly as you typed it — including HTML and JavaScript
                        code</strong>.
                </p>
                <p>
                    If you write a <code>&lt;script&gt;</code> tag in your message, the browser will
                    <strong>execute it as real code</strong> for every visitor who sees the page.
                </p>

                <h4 class="mt-2">🎯 Try These Payloads</h4>
                <ul>
                    <li><code>&lt;script&gt;alert(&apos;XSS&apos;)&lt;/script&gt;</code> — pops an alert box</li>
                    <li><code>&lt;img src=x onerror="alert(&apos;Hacked!&apos;)"&gt;</code> — XSS via image error</li>
                    <li><code>&lt;script&gt;document.body.style.background=&apos;red&apos;&lt;/script&gt;</code> —
                        changes page</li>
                    <li><code>&lt;script&gt;alert(document.cookie)&lt;/script&gt;</code> — steals cookies (try while
                        logged in!)</li>
                </ul>

                <h4 class="mt-2">🛡️ How to Fix It</h4>
                <p>Always <strong>escape/sanitize</strong> user input before displaying it. In EJS, use
                    <code>&lt;%= %&gt;</code> (auto-escapes) instead of <code>&lt;%- %&gt;</code> (renders raw HTML).
                    Also add a Content Security Policy (CSP) header.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>